    <p>
      The equal sign here <c>=</c> doesn’t mean the same as it does in a
      mathematical equation where it implies that the two sides are equal. Here
      it means set the value in the memory location associated with the variable
      name on the left to a <em>copy</em> of the value on the right. The first
      line above sets the value in the box called score to 4. A variable always
      has to be on the left side of the <c>=</c> and a value or expression on
      the right.
    </p>

